values:
Even watching You've Got Mail has me convinced I have become a mean person. Everyone always used to tell me that I was the "nicest" person they have ever met. Or, "one of the nicest." Or perhaps, "generous" or, "very kind." Lately, I keep chopping down people just because. I don't like it. But, it keeps happening. It's like I can not help myself. I especially do this to those that I care about the most. I am so beside myself. I used to live by that rule from Bambi, "If you don't have something nice to say don't say anything at all." 


Oh my movie vice: You've Got Mail

" Do you ever feel you've become the worst version of yourself? That a Pandora's box of all the secret, hateful parts - your arrogance, your spite, your condescension - has sprung open? Someone upsets you and instead of smiling and walking away, you zing them? 'Hello, it's Mr Nasty.' I'm sure you have no idea what I'm talking about. "

" Wouldn't it be wonderful if I could pass all my zingers to you? And then I would never behave badly and you could behave badly all the time, and we'd both be happy. But then, on the other hand, I must warn you that when you finally have the pleasure of saying the thing you mean to say at the moment you mean to say it, remorse inevitably follows."



The remorse is the worst part. I am proud of myself for being so clever, so sharp, so witty, for about .5 seconds. Immediately afterward I want to crawl under anything I can find. I am a mean person. I have become a mean person. And I always try to justify my callous comments too. There is no justification for being a jerk.

Eh. Putting off a phone call. I've never made this type of call before. Telling the guy that Krista just deamed, "The Love of My Life" to tell him he deserves someone and/or something better than who I am/ what we are. He treated me like a princess. He gave me his friendship, his heart, his undying affection, and he gave me freedom. For half a year it all worked out well. I was head over heels-- couldn't ask for anything more. Shane planned to marry me. Yes, it was that serious. Then, I cheated.It was dream-like--- I figured that learning to live in the present... learning to live for the moment is part of my path. It's not. And, it shouldn't be. Shane wished I could turn my emotions on and off the way he does but I don't have that luxury. I'm not a lustful person. I just never fall out of love with the people I've become close to. If I've ever told you I loved you--- I STILL DO... in some respect. Basically I don't regret what I did... I regret the fact that it hurts someone I care about. A wise young man once said, "Guys change about as often as girls forget." My decision to not take that statement and write it across my heart as a reminder has resulted in a momentary loss of my mind. "A successful marriage requires falling in love many times, ALWAYS WITH THE SAME PERSON." - Mignon McLaughlin
What happens if you fall in love with one person and your heart is still wrapped up in another? Red flags. I talk about this issue with my one confidant and even after his warnings I keep moving forward with my hopes held high. Tell me why I talk about an issue--- recognize the dangers ahead.... and keep on going!? I suck at life. I believe that the true measure of a person is how he or she treats everyone regardless of how those people affect their lives. I used to treat everyone I encountered, friend, family member, lover, school mate, or stranger, with the same respect. Not recently.  Demahsa is ashamed spelled backward.



1:50 am text from Shane, "Are you ripping my heart out again?" 

How can I reply?

You can't say you are sorry when your head and your heart are in two different places. I just want to be alone. I've never been a confident girl in any sense of the word confident. However, I have always been able to describe myself using words like: kind, gentle, honest, caring, and everyone's favorite "nice." 

I suppose I'm not the "nice" girl that I always wanted to be. I've disappointed my family and myself so much in the past few months--- it's crazy. They are disgusted with me. I'm somewhat disgusted with myself. For once it's not my physical appearance that makes my stomach churn. It's the bullshit I have been putting people through. Everyone is allowed to make mistakes. Everyone is allowed to feel somewhat lost or confused from time to time. Nonetheless, I draw the line of justified actions at confusion. I'm a cheater and a fake. Cheater in a sense that I was in a relationship filled with trust, compassion, communication, and love and i ruined all of those components within a single evening. Never giving into life's many temptations is something I used to pride myself in. Who am I?

So I flew across the country to see my amazing boyfriend. I met his parents, I spent time with a house-full of Philly-boys, I watched movies, cuddled, kissed, and fell in love over and over again. I'd give anything to be with him every minute of every day. He makes me feel beautiful. I've never loved anyone like this....

What I learned between Friday and Monday is that I now believe in many things I never thought possible....My heart has found a new clarity.

 

I believe:

That hope survives

That trust prevails

That my love abounds

That faith in a relationship triumphs

That optimism predominates

That wishes can conquer

and

That prayers are answered.





p.s. i'm going back in october. nothing and no one will keep me from marrying this boy. and he just called me singing, "I want my baby back,baby back, baby back..." **So cute**

At school... taking a break from Tessellations. Seriously, it take a lot of thought to make these cute shapes I'm creating. I love being a creative person, the only thing is, I let my mind wander too far away from whats important. Instead of actually drawing the right vectors I'm making sure I have the proper arrangement of fuschia and yellow and baby blue. Pfft. Baby blue. See, here goes that mind wandering thing.

I always look forward and backward and forget about what is happening right here, right now. In one month, at this time, I'll be in Wisconsin. But, instead of living in the moment, and being thrilled to see Shane; I bet I will be doing two things. 1.) I will looking into the future---worried about upcoming homework assignments and 2. ) I will looking back, at the relationships I've single-handedly ruined in years past and hoping that Shane doesn't get tired of me. He trusts me. That's a plus. But he doesn't believe me when I tell him all the guys I've liked in the past could care less about me. For some reason he's convinced that I'll go back to an "ex-" or I'll finally meet the guy of my dreams right here in Towson. Cha'right! I met that guy. He lives in Phillips. He just doesn't understand that the distance really means nothing to me. I just have more time for school and friends. If he were here I'd get nothing accoomplished. I don't know what we're going to do when he finds a house. Eep!


Don't get me wrong. I'm incredibly happy. Shane is practically flawless. He makes me smile for hours and hours. Just thinking about being his is nice. I like belonging to someone. And, of course, the flip side--him being mine. That's pretty awesome too. I talked to his roomate Ian for a while the day before yesterday. The two of them apparently brag about Shane's "adorable girlfriend in Maryland." It's funny to me. They're both these gorgeous, hard-working guys, and yet, in their home town... they attract no attetion from the girls. I'm almost worried to move out there because the girls are nothing like me. I'll stand out like a sore thumb.I'm still thinking the girls there will open their eyes one of these days and realize that he's like PERFECT. I swear they must be some dumb chicks. He cooks, he cleans, he works hard all day, he has a nice big new truck, a nice big house, he can pick me up off the groud, he's great with kids, he's fun, he's hott as hell, he doesn't smoke, he's not a drunk, he's never done anything with anyone aside from kissing. Yea, I'm dating a saint. The only down-side is that he makes me feel like a devil-child.

Here I'm pretty good at fading into the background.  And that's really something I like to do. I'm not a girl who likes the spotlight. Unless we're one on one. If it's just me and a friend (or me and Shane) I don't mind soaking up attention for brief periods. But, in large groups, (thats anything greater than 3), I would rather listen, learn, and add comments here and there. With my guy friends. I'm a nice girl, a little sister, a big sister, a mommy-figure,maybe even one-of-the-guys in some instances. However I am not "hott" or "sexy" or by any means "datable." Perhaps it's because the guys here know better. I told Shane time and time again that I'm a handful. And he basically thinks I'm just looking for an excuse to leave. Truthfully, I've made plenty of mistakes in the past. They were not intentional mistakes but they cost me friendships, and reltionships that I thought would have spanned a lifetime. I hated the spats of drama. Circles and circles of supposed "friends" create issues that could have been avoided now that I take a deeper look into it all. He said she said is so silly. In spite of everything.... and all the horrid name-calling that followed. I thought for a while I was a nice girl caught up in a nice boy. I'm guessing now that I was wrong.

"No love, no friendship, can cross the path of our destiny without leaving some mark on it forever."

-Francois Mauriac

On the bright side. Not all bridges have been burned. For example, take Justin Lloyd. I hardly saw him (or the rest of APK) during the time I was with Weber. Contrary to popular belief, that was not because Weber didn't want me to hang out with him, but because we were both seriously busy and I rarely went to shows when he was in town. Nonetheless, he's still one of the best friends I ever had, and I have been talking to him a lot lately. I miss him like crazy. Thankfully, he's not on tour. And we're going to hang out next week. 

Another example, Ryan Hohl. Friends with him since uh... 9th grade. Yesterday was his birthday. All I said was "happy birthday." And now we're making plans to go to an Oriole game. Which sounds like a phenomenal idea to me-huge O's fan- all my plans from May-July baseball wise have been ruined. 

My next small concern, is the whole skirt thing. Yes, I'm trying to branch out of wearing jeans when it's 102 degrees outside. But to me, capris suffice. Shane teamed up with Megan and now they've got me attempting to wear little short jean skirts. That's just not me. I've been told they look nice on me... but honestly I feel like an imposter after 20 minutes in them. Oh well, I'll try my best to warm up to the idea. And I'll keep trying on skirts day in and day out until my comfort level increases.


Today... plans with Megan & my Abby; tonight- Maria and "D." 
I'm actually off work. WTF!?>!

...wrote this years ago for my friend Justin Lloyd... somehow it fits today.


as i wear my heart on my sleeve
you claim to be an open book
but you are wrong
you can lie with a straight face 


confide in me just once
and tell me all there is
empty your soul
pour it in a glass

allow me just one sip

just enough
to quench my thirst
and my thoughts are yours
innocent confessions seep

why the complicated glances?
i can not read your eyes
speak now, here with me
my attention is yours

momentary fears have vanished
thrown away my cautiousness
replace my inquiries with answers
hear my voice

may i console you
i do not wish to intrude
let me be your confidant
trust in me

I'm 20 now. 


My week was starting out pretty cruddy:

-I got a scholarship that was enough to cover the remainder of my tuition this yearbut I have to commit myself to teaching in-state for 2 years :o(

-The tire rod underneath my car broke---causing me to nearly crash into 3 oncoming vehicles

-I missed the Os game with Chuck, Sara, Ashley, Dave, Mel, Cameron, and Andy because of my mangled car

-I had to spend $275 getting my car fixed

-Shane has had to work doubles 4 day in a row (thats a shift from 1 p.m. till 4 a.m.)

-My research paper was not formatted properly---resulting in a B+ 

-That B+ was the worst grade Id ever gotten in college until the next day when I found out I only earned a B on my math exam                                                                                                                                                              

-None of my cd players are working 

-Used my Moms Saturn for a while no A/C in 100 degree weather

-Moms Saturns battery died leaving me stranded when I was supposed to be at work

- I fell off my ladder onto the floor banging my head one morning

-My Verizon Bill was through the roof from texting so much last month

-A transformer blew so I was without power the night I needed to submit my final assignments for my technology course via digital drop box 

And my professor submitted our final grades to the registrar (without my two assignments) so Im going to have an A- or a B+ on my transcript

 

 

However, today was, by far, the BEST birthday I have ever had:

****Nick called, just after midnight, while the power was out and my phone was dead, and he was the first person to wish me a happy birthday via voicemail <3. Shane was still at work           he texted me at 12:21 a.m. Happy, happy, 20th baby doll. Aw, you are all growed up. I miss you and I wish I could give you your birthday kisses now.  I love you. XoXo. Sorry Im            late.

****Shane got home from work just as our power came back on, somewhere around 4 a.m. and he called me to wish me a happy birthday and he sang me a lullaby so I could go to bed a         little earlier than usual.

****I got a good nights sleep for the first time in two weeks and I woke up to a text from Shane, I wouldnt be able to sleep if you were here next to me.  I wish I was there to make you         birthday breakfast. Miss u. Love u lots. Talk to you in a few hours.  

****5:00 a.m. Got up, drew some triangles before class, and talked to my Mom about the wireless connection not working on my laptop. She gave me good news--- my car was fixed.

****7:30 a.m. Picked up my car, drove to school, singing to myself, and called Shane left the sleepy head a voicemail and took a nap in my car once I got to Towson.

****9:30 a.m. my professor told me he wanted to cancel class he felt so crappy but confessed that he didnt want to disappoint me so he kept us till 11:30 and gave us NO HOMEWORK for the first time in weeks. Amy called as I was getting out of class and wished me a happy birthday. Shell be in D.E. for a few days and hopefully we will hang out soon.

****12:15 p.m. Shane received the package I sent him and called me to tell me how excited he was asking permission to open it. So cute!

****12:20ish Called Andy, I was out of class early and way ahead of my schedule so him and I went and got Ritas. Also called Chuck to make sure we were still on for whatever we were doing in the afternoon after I visited Grandma.

****12:30ish Came home to a Petal Pushers van parked in front of my house and a beautiful Jamie <3

**** 1:00ish Called Ms. Kim and thanked her to high heaven for the gorgeous flower arrangement the family sent me: purple and white daisies, purple roses, butterflies, and a huge butterfly balloon. She also gave me fresh veggies from the garden <3

****1:30ish- Stopped at my Grandmas and stayed to chat with Poppy. Andy and Lillie Mae got along really well while  Jamie and skimmed through black and white photos of my grandparents when they were younger. Grandma and Poppy gave me money toward Wisconsin and a beautiful locket for my birthday.

**** Came home and chilled with my Jamie and Andy. Jamie gave me a bucket full of manicure pedicure supplies and the MOST AWESOME lounge chair ever. It matches my IKEA carpet!  Its big, its comfy, its perfect!

**** Mom washed and waxed my car as her gift to me for my birthday. (Several people have hit my car and she even buffed out most of the ugly scratches from the collisions). I stayed long enough to help her and Jamie peel off the stupid stickers on the back of my window. Then I Took Andy home I stole him for way too long visited Ms. Kim, Joe, and Raven.Jamie and Ms. Kim had a talk about puppies it was cute.

**** Jamie and I headed to Chucks. Between Jamie, Chuck, and Mom (as in Chucks mom), my finding airfare for Wisconsin was covered. Mom was on the phone with airlines, Jamie was on the computer looking up some incredible special offers on AirTran and Chuck was helping her from the comfort of his bed. Honestly, Jamie took charge early-on and I wound up  looking through an album of London picture with Chuck while she went to town.

**** Found some amazing flights. Decided it would be in my best interest to stay another night with Shane and come back on the 5th instead of the 4th  and wrote down all of the information so I dont screw it up next week.

**** Chuck made me an amazing mix cd with incredible songs and gave me a card that made it seem like he was not finished the cd silly boy.

****Jamie was hungry. Chuck drove. We all headed to Ruby Tuesday :o)  I stuffed myself.  The two of them took care of the bulk of the bill. Theyre nice like that. Mom called. I had  another delivery.

****Shane sent me daisies! They were dropped off while Jamie, Chuck, and I were playing with cameras and camera phones, texting up a storm, and carrying on like little nerds.

**** I received texts and calls from people all day wishing me a happy birthday I never knew so many people actually cared to notice I was turning 20: Lara, Ryan, Zach, Dave, Jamie, Aunt Melly, Kenna, Tifferz, Megan, Shane, Dustin, Uncle Jeff, Shane again and again,  Maria, Anna, Aunt Melly, my cousin Sarah, Daddy, Grandma, Stacerz, John, Dan, Ashley,     Warren and my Aunt Martha.

****Came home to see my flowers and open gifts from my family. A basket of daisies with a few sweetheart roses stuffed in between <3 <3 and a note, Happy Birthday Baby Doll. Sorry I couldnt be there with you. Hope these flowers put a smile on your face. Love Always, Shane.

****Not long after I got home Chuck let me know that I left my cd at his house we're getting together tomorrow after close so I can get it then but I was bummed because I wanted Maria and Dustin to hear it.

****Opened gifts with Mom, Dad, and Katie: Katie bought me GhostBusters Season1&2! I have a few POUNDS of pistachios, new make-up, and.Daddy got me a new camera phone   Chuck, Maria, Jamie, and I will have good fun with that. The girls try to send me picture messages all the time forgetting my current phone can not display them :o) Heh.

****New text from Shane: Hey baby. Hope you are having a good birthday. I forwarded some money into Dustins account to pay for your birthday dinner. I love you have a good night.

That boy. He's going to be the death of me. Hes sneaky. I cant believe he paid for everyones dinner tonight! Ive never been so spoiled. Katie and I even had 2 desserts! 

****Stacy called several times asking when we would show up at the Harbor. I had no idea. And, I wasnt rushed. Dustin and Maria came over around 6:15.

**** Daddy was happy to me Dustin (because hes a nice guy and because hes Shanes older brother) he also enjoyed seeing my Maria as always---shes the best.

****Maria and Dustin got me a Gift Card to Barnes and Nobles. which is where I was trying to head all day. 

**** We went to the harbor and waited around in the heat for Stacy, John, and Aunt Mel. Dustin let me know just how much Shane gave him for my dinner and it became clear that we     could ALL eat anywhere. I selected Hard Rock but they were only seating the deck. Not cool. We waited for the family some more. And decided to hit up Hooters or something   instead.

**** Everyone had already eaten so Stace, John, and Aunt Mel headed to the Aquarium while we all went to dinner at UNOs. Maria and Dustin got the staff to sing to me they were loud to say the very least.

**** Again, I was missing Shane. He texted me thanking me for his package again and asked if I was having a good birthday. I was, but I wished he could be there.

****We all went to Barnes and Nobles. Maria and I are elementary education majors so naturally we spent half of forever in the childrens lit. section. I used my gift card for a new                      planner, three classic childrens books, and an awesome book mark that Katie picked out. It was orange. She fell in love with it.

****Maria and Dustin read books with eachother--- Stacy showed up and shopped like crazy picking up some really good deals.

****I read a book called I love you a hug and a peck which made me think of Shane. Im sending him that and a small red Corvette A.S.A.P.  hehe   :o)

**** We were all exhausted so we headed home and I thanked them for being so great all evening. Aunt Melly slipped me money for my flight. Obviously, shed heard that Im headed out in September. 

 

I had a blast.

~*~*~*~~*~*
Yesterday,
Emmie, Chase, and Madyson threw me a surprise birthday party. They bought me adorable presents, made me incredibly creative cards, a huge banner that read, "We love you MISS BETH," cake, ice-cream, the whole works. I had the kids from 6:30 a.m. till 4:00 p.m. Took them to the mall, my house, and to Madyson's scrap booking class. Loved every minute of it. Especially when Chase said "NO!" to my little dog Holly when she tried to eat his PB&J. Haha. He doesn't usually speak. So it was huge.

Went to work at LHBP around 5. Shortly after my Poppy was rushed to the hospital. I was worried sick. Chuck visited me and I basically just wanted him to hug me so I could feel like everything was going to be okay. Took a break (at Levi's) so that I could be distracted. But,Stacy and Mom called the store every couple of minutes with updates. None of the doctors know what is wrong. But, they still have him there. Running all sorts of tests. The entire family thought it was best that I stay at the store... because I'm emotional and blah blah. So, Chuck and I went out to DnD after work. He got my mind off some of the not-so-good stuff, taught me how to burn cd's, looked at pictures of me and the kids, let me listened to some tracks from a cd he just made me, and we witnessed history in the making when two women told the mean-angry DnD guy, "No. No. Stop that. Shoo! Just stop. Please. NO!" We cracked up. Never in the history of Dorsey Road DND visits have any of us said anything to the incredibly rude, incredibly grumpy old man. But these women were livid. I loved it.

Chuck likes my shirt. I never wore it in front of him before. He won't admit it. But, he loves it. 

Headed to the hospital now. Apparently Poppy is "out of it." This morning Dad told me that Pop claims he "Slept like a baby." When his nurse says, "He hardly slept at all. We found him wandering around looking for 'Lillie Mae' "   (Lillie is his dog... at home.) FYI- Poppy is one of the three guys in my life that have never made me cry. He's my FAVORITE person in the entire world. And he was fine just two days ago. I'm still worried sick. And I don't really know what to say or do.

Let's see. Highlights....
 
-Went to see "Me and my Gal" with Maria, Momma Italian, and Dustin last night... they laughed at me and Shane texting back and forth like crazy kids
-Dustin let me know that his brother has never been this happy (and that made me feel incredible.)
-Also got lectured about never saying "Melk" hahaha.
-Abby is all kindsa happy...which makes me happy...because we're both like glowing.
-Chuck and I went to DnD two nights ago. I showed him where we need to visit in London via postcards. Also came up with a master plan involving Japan and Wisconsin. 
-Made a giant card that will be in the mail on Monday.
-Talked to Daddy about moving.
-Megan and I went on a shopping rampage on Friday <3 A&E Jeans, Disney Store, Forever 21, Build-a-Bear,Chicken Nuggets...Good Fun.
-The crew is getting together on Tuesday for an Orioles game <3 it will be super fun--- I think I will bring Ashley because it's our birthday thing.
-I was going to another O's game Friday with Andy but they called me into work (huge surprise).
-Still thinking about a conversation I had with Chuck.
**Note to self: Why would they call something a circus if there is no circus?**
-Shane and I were on the phone till 3 a.m. again yesterday.
"I'd give anything to be with you right now. I wish I could hold you. I told my roomate how incredible you are. And I never have felt this comfortable around anyone in my entire life. Twenty two years and I found the person I've always wanted. If I had the money for a ring....well... basically my roomate said I need to pack my bags and get to Maryland."
 

**sigh** C'mon September.

To sum up my weekend:


Pirates 2 w/ the family.
Designed new shirts for the fall.
Lots of time at L.H.B.P.
Math homework.
Research.
Mikayla,Kyle,Alexis, Alicin,Alyssa = Best kids ever
Sarah & Greg (my big brother) <3 <3 <3
New shoes! Megan's fault.
Jamie is angry with me :o(
Great store meeting--- I got kudos. 
I'm still behind on homework.
"I think I found something worth coming back for."
Megan is a terrific shopping buddy/Smoothie Maker <3
No one could get me to stop smiling even if they tried.
21 hours is a long way away.
Nana <3
The moon has looked amazing for 3 nights in a row.
Cheesecake Factory; MmmmMmM
Someone thinks I'm beautiful.
16 Blocks
Enchanted Apple from Victoria's.
I want a plane ticket for my birthday.
1 Ipod+ 4 Dashboard Albums + Playing Pool + UNO= Best night of my entire summer



Tomorrow....Entourage at Dave's house.  <3 Woo.

Hmmm. Where to begin. Jamie and I were up till after 3 am (when I had to leave for work this morning no later than 6:30) because we love eachother and I was so happy to have her here. She kept wiggling around in the water bed saying "wiggle wiggle wiggle," then she  cuddled with me till I was asleep. Pretty much love Jamie. Wish I could marry her but that's Danny's job. I was sad because I wanted to show her off to Dan last night but he was feeling under the weather. Poor sickeepoo. I hope he's feeling better now. 

I was so happy to see Emilie and Chase today. It was insane. I picked Emilie off the ground and spun her around like twenty times telling her how beautiful she was. Her reply, "I missed you too Miss Beff. Next time you come on bacation too. What's for breakfast?!" LoL. Chase was so handsome and manly when he woke up around 8:30. First of all, the child NEVER sleeps that late. Second, I'm usually greeted by a cute smiling baby, not one that is jumping out of the crib paratrooper style into my arms and growling <3 <3 I taught him to growl like a lion just before they left. I'm guessing he just wanted to show me that he remembered.Aw. 


I baked muffins for the kids, Oma, and Pop Pop. We danced around the kitchen ...like always. And then we went upstairs and "exercised." Emilie makes up her own version of crunches and it's priceless. Chase napped for the rest of the morning while Emmie and I watched Sprout and cut out shapes. The day went by incredibly fast.

Jamie, Mom, Dave, and someone else called me throughout the morning. I'm not sure who the fourth person was--but I didn't answer. Dave was confirmed plans for tomorrow night because he's awesome like that. Jamie was just calling to see what was up... and later I had to call her and let her know that I can't go to V.A. beach till Friday afternoon for our concert. Kelly Clarkson <3 Needless to say Jamie Lynn is really upset. And I can understand why. But, I really need to watch the kids Friday morning and they have no one else available. Mom called to talk to me about an indian reservation they visited. My family is so adorable and random. Their vacation is scattered in four states. Wtf!? Every day they call me to tell me, "We wish you were here." And I can not wait for next summer when I can be a part of their unorganized chaos. 

In the afternoon I was headed to Chuck's. He had an eye appointment at ten and I thought he would be recovered by 12:30 but he wasn't. So I went home and played with the dogs...then I called again. He was out running errands "for his mom" which somehow included taking Megan lunch. And, I had to wait. I'm used to the waiting..... so I passed the time at Linthicum Library. I read children's books for an hour or more when Chuck called to say he was on his way home. Then he texted me to ask if I was still coming. Of course I was! We watched the last episode of the second season of Entourage. It really is the best show I've ever watched. Chuck will be taping all of the third season so I can catch up. The ending wasn't sad like I thought so I was pleased. I brought over Empire Records, a great movie, and one that I haven't seen in ages. We'll have to watch that tomorrow because we had better things to do, and 40 minutes before we had to be at work. 

Speaking of work, they've called me in everyday of the entire summer. Even on days when I AM SCHEDULED...they call me in early and/or ask me to stay late. I love being needed....I love knowing that I actually serve a purpose and that they depend on me- but I promise you I have a life. Bleh. So, went home, changed into a skirt, a tank, some heels, and ran to Arundel Mills. 

Dave's first day at Levi's and we're already taking breaks at the same time :o) Mall neighbors are FuN. I also ran into Suzanne and Adam during my break. Suzanne said I looked skinny and tan. I love that. She's like little as hell and she said I'm skinny. Which, is also what Rachel said when I ran into at the mall a few days back. I don't think I will ever get tired of hearing that. I may deny it and think people are delusional---but it's nice to be complimented. In the afternoon, before work, I realized that Dave and Chuck were BOTH closing and we made plans to get coffee. It was just Michelle and I for the majority of the evening. Poor Krista felt sick so she went home early-- and I was quite happy to get out of the store at 10:05. Went to DnD on Dorsey *they're all kinds of nice.*  Psssh. The man who works the night shift has the personality of a brick, he doesn't smile, he takes 6 years getting to the counter to take an order, and, he slams around chairs and sweeps/mops right beneath us every time we go. Oh well, it's better than running into people at the DnD on B&A I suppose. 

Our conversation was hilarious. I laughed so much my face hurt. Dave must think I'm insane. Chuck knows me well enough to know what I'm thinking...but when I say my "thoughts" out loud Dave sits there like "WHAT!?" We unleashed comment after sarcastic comment and I can't repeat what flew from our mouths. I had a grand time and I'm excited that tomorrow night we will all be together again at Ellen's house.

Chuck and I have plans tomorrow morning/afternoon. I do not have to be at work till three so we should be able to watch at least one movie. I'm going to try to let him sleep in a little bit. Came home, checked my MySpace, and tried to fit some more clothing in my closet. Message from Melz about how she's happy I'm coming out with everyone again, also gave me directions to Ellen's. I loved spending time with her and thinking about being "cool" again is nice. Terrifying but nice. But, I'm assuming she sent me a message because she's hanging out with Weber again. I'm not stupid. I actually remember Ms. Kim's exact words the first time Amy was up in his room, "She's not your friend if she's trying to get with your man." Heh. I don't blame Amy really. I'm trying to remember some of them....apparently I slept with Alex and Warren on the same day. Ha. I have nothing terribly mean to say. Weber made it sound like she was all over him back in the day...which made me uncomfortable for the longest time... but I have no claim on him now. So, have fun. 


Sarah and Greg are home. They called yesterday and I nearly cried. I miss my cousins. I'm hoping to see them on Thursday after class--- since I can't head to Virginia. I will def. see everyone at my aunt's on Saturday though. I'm sure I'll be the brave one in the pool with all the kids. It won't be the same without Anna. I'm sure there will be a lot of tears.

Warren just called me again. At 1:30 a.m. He seems to do that a lot. I don't know why it's always 1:30 a.m. Eh. Alcohol. He's trying. I really don't care. The conversation was about 90 seconds long. He's drunk and texting/calling because I don't want anything to do with him. Beer...I'm so glad thats not my thing. I elected NOT to go to Tricia's party tonight for that very reason. I love those girls. They're sweethearts for inviting me; but I haven't been exposed to all of them being trashed at once since highschool. I miss them nonetheless. Others are convinced that it will solve all of my problems. Which is funny. Because I don't have any problems at the moment. In fact, I'm quite happy.

I'll make this brief because I have a beautiful bestest friend spending the night. Today was uneventful until AFTER I got off work. Watered the garden, did my pilates, watched a bit of television(which I never do), fed the dogs, fed the fish, called Grandma, figured out that Chuck would be unavailable, went tanning and came home. I ate some more canned fruit. Grandma left canned fruit on my railing the other day. She loves me. And, she is well aware that i eat nothing here at the house. So far I've finished off one can of fruit cocktail, one can of pear halves, and some pineapple. I was sad that I couldn't see Chuck. I'm dying for someone to watch my new movies with me....but I'm sure Jamie and I will knock out one tonight. Went to work at 2:30. Showed up to two tremendously long lines and a stressed Key Holder. She said I was, "supposed to be in at two." I was scheduled 3-9; I've had the schedule since the day Stacy made it in early June. However, someone whited out my shift inside the back room and changed me to 2-8. Good to know... I've never been late for anything in my entire life. Needless to say I was very upset. I had three voicemails during my break. One from my parents, who are SUPPOSED TO BE IN TENNESSEE...they're currently in North Carolina ((random)), one was from Jamie <3 my date, and the other was from Nick. Crazy. He's never called me before. I called Nick back and we made plans for this Wednesday. I'm beyond excited about that. I had to get back to work because the store was packed so I cut our convo short and called Jamie to confirm our evening. We were busier than we are during the holidays--we made over $6,000 in five hours. Nothing really special. Customers that hugged me for giving them good bras. It was cute. I got out at 8 :o) and there was Jamie sitting in front of the store. We got tickets for The Devil Wears Prada. We had an hour to kill so we ate. And I talked her ear off. We went to Remomo's.. I had spinach and crab dip, Jamie had a salad, and we split dessert. The movie was great. Adrian Grenier co-starred. Jamie and I loved him in "Drive Me Crazy" but now I get to see him in Entourage. He's only gotten cuter over time. Nonetheless, the movie made me want to go shopping and I am very glad that the mall was closed when we got out of the movie otherwise I would have spent a LOT of money. Jamie and I headed to DnD, recieved some free donuts, got some coffee, and now we're ready for movies. <3 goodnight.

I think of the word OBLIGATION in a semi-negative context. To me, an obligation is when you find yourself bound to something and you have no choice in the matter. Arranged marriages are an obligations, family reunions are an obligation, physical examinations, are an obligation. An obligation is an act of unwanted commitment that you've imposed upon yourself or that has been imposed upon you by a higher power. I am obligated to tell my parents where I am and where I will be throughout the day because I love and respect them. I am obligated to be home at a decent time, I am obligated to pay my bills, I'm obligated to go to class.... but I am by no means happy about having to do all of these things.

Anyway, I made myself a livejournal. I really do not know why. Perhaps its because Chuck showed me my old Xanga several days ago and it made me miss having a place to rant. Perhaps it's because I can not read all of Chuck's archives without having my own L.J. account. Perhaps it's 11 p.m. and I'm bored to death. Regardless of the situation I'm glad I have taken a moment or two to create an account and we'll see where things go from here.

<3
